<font color="#FF0000">BARBARIANS AT THE GATE</font><br>
<tt>Sat Aug 30 23:15:28 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
BARBARIANS AT THE GATE<br>
                Sat Aug 30 23:10:17 US/Eastern 1997 <br><br>
                For a long time this site held to high standards, of intellectual discourse, of<br>
                emotional healing, of the likes of Tanker, DocDel, Chet, Professor, and others,<br>
                many others.<br>
                We fought out our boundaries and established our positions. We gradually learned<br>
                to learn from each other, and to respect each other.We shared our feelings and we<br>
                grew. <br><br>
                Then, like a virus, the site got invaded and changed. Code names replaced real<br>
                ideas. Gory stories replaced emotional release. Macho braggards replaced sincere<br>
                veterans. Bullshit replaced real emotions. Brave names and secred codes replaced<br>
                open honesty and men brave enough to talk about their guts.<br><br>
                Is this the normal cycle of a site? I don't know. It is like we started out with praise<br>
                and poetry, emotions and depth, and ended up at the wrong end of Conan the<br>
                Barbarian.<br>
                I grieve for the former, and I am repulsed by the latter.<br><br>
                The fact that one of the most prominent writers now has his own agenda, I mean<br>
                book and it is so obvious. Others have their native roots to push. Some can't stand<br>
                alone and are doomed to flip-flop back and forth. But above all, or possibly below<br>
                all, is the tune: &quot;Macho Macho man, I want to be a Macho man.&quot;<br><br>
                We used to have a site of sharing, of healing, of growing. Now we have a site of<br>
                gory, of murder, of killing &quot;gooks&quot; and &quot;commies&quot; and we have lost something<br>
                with this new generation of &quot;posters.&quot; We have lost the ability of critical thinking.<br>
                Of daring to think differently. Of questioning authority and the established norm. Of<br>
                dropping the &quot;commie bull shit line&quot; and moving beyond it. We used to have<br>
                Vietnamese contributors, now they have headed for the hills, or their bunkers,<br>
                knowing that this site in now hostile for them.<br><br>
                As a result, we have lost most of our original writers. Gone is DocDel, Tanker,<br>
                Sarge666, most of Chet, and many, many others. I understand that they don't want<br>
                to wallow in the mud with the new boys. That is their right, and I respect it. I just<br>
                pine for it.<br><br>
                It just is a damn shame to see the site change this way. Perhaps it had to. Perhaps<br>
                Kali Tai and her bullshit site will reigh supreme after all (sixties-L project). But<br>
                before the magic names and Indian hoo-rah, before the macho &quot;kill the commies&quot;<br>
                jargon, there once was a place of feelings, of raw emotions, like real group therapy,<br>
                where one could talk and dump, and no-one stuck him in the side with a pig sticker,<br>
                and the group encouraged him to continue. Now the site is more a battle field. Not a<br>
                therapy group or a meeting of old friends. I am so sorry for this turn of events, even<br>
                though I didn't start it, couldn't stop it,<br>
                and wish to hell it never happened.<br><br>
                All I can do is call upon the old posters, the old writers, to get involved again. Stem<br>
                the tide brothers and SISTERS. (I know you are out there sisters, I hope you have<br>
                not fled). Reclaim our land, our land. We don't have to give up in silence. Express<br>
                your disgust and light up this site. This is our last stand, before the hordes of the<br>
                barbarians blow open our gate. Who will stand with me? Will you not join me in a<br>
                site for sharing of feelings, instead of bragging about killing, of growth, instead of<br>
                death? Come on Lads and Lassies, the time is nigh, and there is work aplenty.
<p><code>-- posted  (doc spatz) </code><p>


